description.narrative: Key results in 2019 include the release of the MICS6 data, with UNICEF support, providing up to date data on the situation of children and women in Tunisia, informing 140 indicators on health, nutrition, early childhood development, education and protection, including 40 child-related SDG indicators. The survey, fourth of its type, highlights progress for children and disparities in achieving outcomes for children, particularly linked to the child living setting and socio-economic status. The survey and database are public, providing a wealth of data for further analysis, research, and evidence-based advocacy and policy formulation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/01/2020
